<p>Now I write C# code after the PHP.</p>  <p>In PHP I create a hierarchy of exceptions guided by the recommendations of the Zend Framework(Symfony now use something similar).</p>  <p>In package(for example Order) I create folder Exception, in this folder(translate from php to C#):</p>  <pre><code>namespace Order.Exception {     interface ExceptionInterface{}     class ApplicationException : System.ApplicationException, ExceptionInterface{}     class OrderNotFoundException : ApplicationException {}     class SomethingHappensException : ApplicationException{} } </code></pre>  <p>I need a lot of exceptions(relatively) to conveniently express the things from domain.</p>  <p>Is there any have good practices to create hierarchies of exceptions?</p>  <p>Technical details of creation I understand completely. The issue of good practice.</p>